-- Turkey's Finansbank secures syndicated loan worth $845 mln 
-- 
-- Tue Nov 25, 2014 04:54AM EST
-- None



ISTANBUL, Nov 25 (Reuters) - Turkey's Finansbank <FINBN.IS>, owned by National Bank of Greece <NBGr.AT>, said on Tuesday it secured a syndicated loan in two tranches of $397 million and 356 million euro ($442.6 million).

The loans will be used to finance foreign trade and has a maturity of 1 year, said the statement to the Istanbul stock exchange.